<br>
As for warriors/tanks, cover the retreat in a running evac situation. You have the hit points, and if you are down low enough that you can't cover the retreat, you should already be zoning, because once you are gone, your casters will die soon after. Casters run when the puller or group leader realizes it's a bad situation (or teleport the group out if you have that capability). Don't hang around to get stunned, hoof it with the rest of the group, maybe tossing a spell or two to allow the person covering the retreat the breathing room to get out as well. <br>
<br>
And if you are in Kedge Keep, make sure the person who cast enduring breath is still there to cast it again when needed. <br>
<br>
