<br>
I think this saves a few seconds, allows you to react quicker to MOB aggro changes.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujaykay.showPublicProfile>Jaykay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#8E9173>(5/13/00 11:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.havenoflight.org/jayweb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Positions for tanks</span><hr size=1> I have noticed that tanks just love to line up in front of mobs, like he is taking their picture. You get a nice attack bonus if you stand behind. Get half of those tanks BEHIND the mob <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
