<br>
- Dots:  Don't bother using this on a blue mobs if you have 2+ tanks in your group. Simply not efficient.  <br>
<br>
- Pack Regen: If you have 2 or less tanks in your group, I would rather use normal regen since it lasts double the time.  Only use Pack Regen if you see more than the tanks hurt on a regular basis<br>
<br>
- SLD for all: I am really curious if the person who wrote the guide is constantly below 50 mana...I for one find it more resourceful to keep it only on the tanks if you are the only healer.  Better yet, get a cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Other casters should be smart enough to not to get hit too much, and to use 200 mana on all members to account for one possible situation does not seem a good use of mana (better to keep enough mana to snare / root and maybe even blast the mob away from the fragile caster.<br>
<br>
