<br>
I don't know if there are just to few Bards or whether people just don't group with them as much at the lower levels. At my current 18th level I hear alot of 'I didn't know you could do that'.<br>
<br>
Bards are utility players, they can do a little of everything, just not as good or as fast.<br>
<br>
Here are my suggestions:<br>
<br>
1) No Enchanter in group - Bard can handle crowd control. He has a mezz song, same rules apply no DOT or DD. All melee types /assist puller. Healer watch the Bards health because as the MOB's break/resist the song they will pummel and stun the Bard till he can start the song again.<br>
<br>
2) Downtime Healing - Healers save your mana for the fight. Bards can handle downtime healing. At my current level of 18 I can heal everybody in the group 10 hp per flash. That is if they are close enough, sitting down and I have my mandolin equipped.<br>
<br>
3) Tank Buffs - Tanks coordinate with the Bard. The Bard has a strength buff + Haste song or an all around strength + dex + agility buff song. If you have weapons that proc you may want the dex + agility buff. I always ask the tanks their preference.<br>
<br>
4) Melee Bard - Bards can tank, sort of. I don't have taunt or the HP to do it for long but, in a pinch I can. Bards get dual wield and can wear plate armor.<br>
<br>
5) Twisting - When grouping with a Bard ask him how many songs he can keep going at once. Good Bards can keep 3 going at once. Thats a heal, strength buff and AC buff. A really good Bard can do that and equip the instrument for that song to give it a bonus. Some can even do 4 songs at once.<br>
<br>
