   Pulling is a major responsibility insofar as stupid pulls get people killed, while on the otherhand a good puller can make a great night for a group. Trust me, people remember you when they have gotten more exp from your pulls in one night than they have from the last 3 pullers put together.<br>
   An excellent puller knows his or her groups strengths and weaknesses. You must be able to the read the people behind the character also, not just the characters abilities but the way the characters are being played is vital in understanding how the group can handle various situations that arise. Rarely, are groups made up of the correct or best classes for the critter being hunted. There several reasons for this but most of the time its too few people available to group with at a particular time and therefore you have to do the best you can with what's at hand. The makeup of the group changes constantly when people need to log and you get new people this means that the puller must re-determine what the group is capable of and as a puller needs to make accurate decisions of group strength based on class, lvl, exp.<br>
   In closing: the best pullers are those that have an innate understanding of the capabilities of a group and an understanding of the needs and wants of a group.<br>
